The framegrabber software uses the v4l (video4linux) API.
This API ships with the current 2.4.25 kernel.  You
must configure the kernel with v4l enabled as a module
plus, the BTTV modules.

In short:

% cd /usr/src/linux
% make menuconfig
 navigate to multimedia devices, select module for v4l
 then select the v4l devices, and enable bttv as a module
 then navigate to character devices from the top level
 select I2C and also select module loading
 Then exit and save kernel config.
% make dep ; make modules ; make modules_install ; make bzImage
 (install the bzImage kernel per normal)
% vi /etc/modules.conf
  Add the following:
    alias char-major-81 bttv
    options bttv card=73 tuner=-1 autoload=0
    options i2c-algo-bit bit_test=1

  card 73 is for the older Sensoray 311 card, but works fine with 711

That's it...

